<subSubSection id="C3466511FFC1FFFD75D1AC03C5F7AA86" pageId="2" pageNumber="508" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE3369AFFC1FFFD75D1AC03C7A2AACF" blockId="2.[151,1436,1550,2009]" pageId="2" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFC1FFFD75D1AC03C71AAA73" bold="true" box="[151,375,1550,1576]" pageId="2" pageNumber="508">Diagnosis. Female.</emphasis>
Body slender, shiny, thorax and legs mainly yellow; postcranium with only a pair of occipital setae behind inner vertical seta; legs without pennate setae; hind tarsomere 1 whitish to silvery, elongate; wing widely brown infuscate mainly in costal and apical margins, base narrowed and anal lobe very narrow; tergites 1 and 2 reddish-brown, shiny.
</paragraph>
